  "name": "Coalition",
  "tutorialKey": "multi_faction_practice",
  "tutorial": {
    "title": "Four corners, one center",
    "body": "The map is split into four quadrants by a stone cross. Each corner holds a faction — you (Water), Water (red), Slime (green), and Blood (crimson). The only way between quadrants is through the central crossroads, and a neutral tower stands at its heart, attacking anyone who crosses.\n\nSlime concocts fast. Blood captures cheaply. Water out-produces. They'll fight each other through the center if you let them — or you can seize the central tower and dictate the engagement.\n\nYou win when all three enemy factions are gone."
  },
  "objective": "Outlast or outplay all three factions. The center tower is the key.",
